      "comment": "FABULOUS DREAM NZ (5) has been excellent so far this prep, winning both of her starts at this circuit and distance. Draws a couple of spots deeper than when she led throughout last week but overcame a much wider barrier to score fresh. Her strike rate here and at the trip stands at 50 per cent. Can land the hat trick. Hard to knock the consistency of A LITTLE SILENCE NZ (9) who has finished top-two in all five starts at this venue since crossing from NZ. May need a bit of luck negotiating a wide starting position but has upside and could keep the ball rolling. SAMMY SUFFARELL (11) draws on the back row but must be respected after scoring by 11 metres at this circuit and distance last week. OFFICIAL ROCK (2) draws much better so can improve second-up.",
